{"tid":1279414,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"Cloudflare CTO澄清並非受到網絡攻擊","createTime":"2019-07-02T16:17:35.000Z","updateTime":"2019-07-02T16:51:33.000Z","uid":29625,"like":14,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":6,"replies":[{"pid":"3c320a36a69ee8bfa76cce4f7b20dc2bcaab2cc4","tid":1279414,"uid":29625,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-02T16:17:35.000Z","msg":"I've seen a bunch of speculation that today's @Cloudflare outage was caused by a DDoS from China, Iran, North Korea, etc. etc. <br />\n<br />\nIt was not an attack by anyone from anywhere.<br />\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/jgrahamc/status/1146078278278635520\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjgrahamc%2Fstatus%2F1146078278278635520&d=DMh58HXBMwQbarqDBIsRc%2FGl%2B26pDsgLotMYn9d4AWI%3D&h=e4370a18\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjgrahamc%2Fstatus%2F1146078278278635520&h=3a6fbb0b\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://twitter.com/jgrahamc/status/1146078278278635520</a><br />\n<br />\nCEO:<br />\nMassive spike in CPU usage caused primary and backup systems to fall over. Impacted all services. No evidence yet attack related. Shut down service responsible for CPU spike and traffic back to normal levels. Digging in to root cause.<br />\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/eastdakota\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Feastdakota&d=DMh58HXBMwQbarqDBIsRc%2FGl%2B26pDsgLotMYn9d4AWI%3D&h=ff9bc088\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://twitter.com/eastdakota</a>"},{"pid":"3a00e89fd549ffe03d5a420c4a97f8db8e88497b","tid":1279414,"uid":29625,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-02T16:18:06.000Z","msg":"第二條link貼錯<br />\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/eastdakota/status/1146065231270907907\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Feastdakota%2Fstatus%2F1146065231270907907&d=DMh58HXBMwQbarqDBIsRc%2FGl%2B26pDsgLotMYn9d4AWI%3D&h=fa5d4cb6\" data-ef-url